# versions.env.example — pin the fleet's container images to exact digests (R3)
# =============================================================================
# WHY: the fleet serves ONE config to EVERY box, so every box must run the SAME
# router image. `:latest` drifts — a box that pulls it later can get a newer
# image whose schema no longer matches the committed poc-strix.yaml (the real
# root cause of a past outage: `runtime_config_load_failed: removed config
# fields ... global.router.model_selection.session_aware`). Pinning a digest
# freezes the image so all boxes are byte-identical.
#
# HOW TO USE:
#   1. cp versions.env.example versions.env        # versions.env is gitignored
#   2. put a REAL digest in versions.env (see below), then just run as usual:
#        HALO_A_IP=... HALO_B_IP=... HALO_B_SSH=... FLEET_MODE=gateway \
#          bash run-all-2box.sh
#      run-all-2box.sh and deploy-fleet-2box.sh auto-source ./versions.env (if
#      present) near the top and FORWARD the pin to every box (Halo-A inherits
#      it locally; each remote box gets it over SSH). Nothing here is required —
#      with no versions.env the recipe behaves exactly as before.
#
# HOW TO GET THE REAL DIGEST (run once on a box that already serves OK):
#   docker inspect --format '{{index .RepoDigests 0}}' \
#     ghcr.io/vllm-project/semantic-router/vllm-sr-rocm:latest
#   # -> ghcr.io/vllm-project/semantic-router/vllm-sr-rocm@sha256:<64-hex>
# Paste the bare `repo@sha256:...` reference (NOT a tag, NOT a URL/Markdown link)
# as VLLM_SR_ROUTER_IMAGE below. ci-check.sh fails if this is not a @sha256 pin.

# --- The vllm-sr ROCm router image (the one that must NOT drift) -------------
# The digest below is a known-good pin for this fleet, validated on the 2-box
# Strix Halo run 20260717 (verify-hardening 8 passed / 0 failed / 1 skipped) and
# pullable from ghcr; VERIFY/refresh it for your environment with the
# `docker inspect` command above before relying on it.
VLLM_SR_ROUTER_IMAGE=ghcr.io/vllm-project/semantic-router/vllm-sr-rocm@sha256:90bfde3027832b15bc5b8ddd4a0790182a8f89858421444d752c6e6d49ffa382

# --- Pull policy for the pinned image ----------------------------------------
# ifnotpresent = pull the pinned digest only if it is not already local (good
# for a freshly provisioned box). Other values: always, never.
VLLM_SR_IMAGE_PULL_POLICY=ifnotpresent

# --- Other images used by gateway mode (informational) -----------------------
# These are set inside gateway-bring-up.sh and are NOT sourced from here today;
# listed so operators know the full image surface of a gateway box:
#   ollama/ollama:rocm                                            (tier-model host)
#   ghcr.io/vllm-project/semantic-router/dashboard:origin-fix      (optional UI)
# If you mirror images into a private registry, retag the router digest above.
